<!-- ============================================================
     § 01 — PILLARS / SOLUTION
     ============================================================ -->
<section id="solutions">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
      <div class="meta">§ 01 / Solution</div>
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">The Watershed Solution</span>
        <h2 style="margin-top:18px;max-width:18ch">An intelligent ATS for institutional options flow.</h2>
        <p class="lead" style="margin-top:18px">Three principles govern every order routed through Watershed — discretion, minimized impact, and a deterministic path to the listed markets. No high-touch desk. No information leakage. No preferential routing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pillars">
      <article class="pillar" data-reveal>
        <div class="pill-head">
          <span class="num">01</span>
          <span class="cat">Discretion</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Discreet, Complete, Compliant</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Clients control who can see orders and their ultimate price is not revealed to Liquidity Providers.</li>
          <li>All trades are executed on National Exchanges — no need for additional clearing arrangements.</li>
          <li>Transaction data is fully compliant with MiFID II and CAT reporting requirements.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="pillar" data-reveal>
        <div class="pill-head">
          <span class="num">02</span>
          <span class="cat">Market Impact</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Minimized Market Impact</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Liquidity Providers selected based on their ability to quote and trade size in volatility markets across the entire term structure.</li>
          <li>Clients control both the information contained in the order and its path to the listed markets.</li>
          <li>Third-party surveillance systems ensure client orders are not moving markets outside the ATS.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="pillar" data-reveal>
        <div class="pill-head">
          <span class="num">03</span>
          <span class="cat">Order Flow</span>
        </div>
        <h3>How Orders Flow</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Orders are routed into a private auction with a select pool of Liquidity Providers.</li>
          <li>Matched Orders are sent to an exchange as a cross ticket with an additional chance for client price improvement at the exchange.</li>
          <li>Entire process is completed faster than any high-touch solution.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


